1933;;To the Last Man;;American;;Henry Hathaway;;Randolph Scott, Esther Ralston;;western;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/To_the_Last_Man_(1933_film);;A feud between the Colby and the Hayden families, starts in the hills of Kentucky and continues in the West after the American Civil War. Also involved is the conflict between vigilantism and the law in a frontier environment, and lovers from the two feuding families. At one point, one of the villains shoots the head off Shirley Temple's character's doll.